---

Types of Food Packaging

1. Primary Packaging

Primary packaging comes into direct contact with the food.

Examples include:

Plastic bottles

Glass bottles

Metal cans

Paper wrappers

Plastic pouches



---

2. Secondary Packaging

Secondary packaging groups several primary packages together.

Examples include:

Cartons

Boxes

Shrink wraps



---

3. Tertiary Packaging

Tertiary packaging is used for transportation and bulk distribution.

Examples include:

Wooden pallets

Shipping containers

Large cartons

Stretch wraps



