Conclusion

Food labeling and packaging are fundamental aspects of food safety and quality assurance. Effective labeling provides consumers with accurate information regarding ingredients, nutrition, allergens, storage conditions, and product identity, enabling informed purchasing decisions. Safe packaging protects food from contamination, preserves quality, and extends shelf life throughout the supply chain. Compliance with national and international regulations, the use of food-grade packaging materials, and accurate labeling practices are essential for protecting public health, reducing food waste, and promoting consumer confidence in the food industry.
